Student-athletes of Division I men’s baseball, excluding historically Black colleges and universities, are white by an overwhelming majority

Of the 11,013 players in 2023, 78 percent identified as white, 18 percent identified as another race, and only 4 percent identified as Black. There is one female student-athlete playing D-I men’s baseball, who identifies as another race.
